Please optimize the following code which sorts an array in a linear manner.
```py
def sort(arr):
    for i in range(len(arr)):
        for j in range(i+1, len(arr)):
            if arr[i] > arr[j]:
                arr[i], arr[j] = arr[j], arr[i]
    return arr

print(sort([3, 1, 4, 1, 5, 9, 2, 6, 5, 3, 5]))
```

